Title: A SEQUENTIAL METROPOLIS-HASTINGS ALGORITHM  
Author: PIERRE VANDEKERKHOVE 
Keyword: Key words. Metropolis-Hastings algorithm, Rate of convergence, Sequential method.  
Address: Pavia, Italy.  
Affiliation: Universita di  
Abstract: This paper deals with the asymptotic properties of the Metropolis-Hastings algorithm, when the distribution of interest is unknown, but can be approximated by a sequential estimator of its density. We prove that, under very simple conditions, the rate of convergence of the Metropolis-Hastings algorithm is the same as that of the sequential estimator when the latter is introduced as the reversible measure for the Metropolis-Hastings Kernel. This problem is a natural extension of previous a work on a new simulated annealing algorithm with a sequential estimator of the energy. 
